Class OSFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • owlSpeak.OSFactory

  • public class OSFactory
extends java.lang.Object

      • getPartitionTree

        public Partition getPartitionTree(java.lang.String user,
                         java.lang.String suffix,
                         OwlSpeakOntology osOnto)
        returns the root partition of the partition tree containing all partitions belonging to one partition distribution specified by its name. The partitions are read from the OWL ontology. Retrieves the root partition identified by name and then performs a breadth-first search using a queue data structure.
        Parameters:
        user - the user name
        suffix - suffix added to user to build the Name of the main (root) partition object.
        osOnto - the OwlSpeakOntology object
        Returns:
        the root partition of the partition tree of partitions belonging to the same partition distribution
